                                                            <div class="elementor-widget-container">
                                                                <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">In Dialer360 the outbound call time is relative to the local time zone of the lead being called. For example, if the campaign&#8217;s call time was set to “9am-5pm”, a lead would not be called until it was at least 9am local time; regardless of what time zone they lived in. For inbound calls, the call time is based on the server time. Anything outside of that time is considered “after hours”.</span></p>
                                                            </div>
                                                        </div>
                                                        <div class="elementor-element elementor-element-4ef9e6f elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading" data-id="4ef9e6f" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="heading.default">
